08/11/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Police launched a massive operation Wednesday (November 7th) and arrested 25 people in the village of Zoniana on Crete.
They were held for a variety of offenses, including illegal possession of weapons, explosives and a small amount of drugs.
The operation, which involved blocking all roads to the village, was aimed at arresting a gunmen involved in a shootout Monday that wounded three police officers.
They had been dispatched to search the home of a local drug lord, known to have large cannabis plantations.
The officers were ambushed by dozens of men armed with assault rifles.
(AFP, Reuters, ANA-MPA, ERT, Kathimerini, DPA - 07/11/07)
